I didn‚Äôt have an addiction to social media, porn, or masturbation, but I did have one to cigarettes.

content.y:
Alright, look, I recommend this: evaluate what you've got - home, family, food, internet access - then think about folks who don't have that. There are countries torn by war. Picture a 19-year-old in Israel whose house just got blown up and has nothing, no food, nada like what you've got.

 Then, think of gratitude. Be thankful to life, the universe, God, luck, and whatever you believe in, just be grateful you're not in that situation. You should feel thankful for everything, from being alive today to having the chance to be here at TRW.

Now, what you gotta do is find your purpose. Finding your purpose is easy - you gotta think about love. Love is the strongest force in the universe, and by thinking about love, you can establish your life's mission. If you look at the folks here at TRW, like the professors, Ace, the Top G, etc. - I guarantee they're living their purpose. 

We as humans only truly grow when we dedicate ourselves to something bigger, something important, something better for us. In other words, we gotta dedicate ourselves to something that benefits others' lives. That's what Top G and the professors do - they strive to help us.

 And I can assure you, deep down, they all feel like they're living their purpose. It's an expression of love, believe it or not, they're literally changing lives. And if you look at any other successful man or woman, they're doing the same thing in their own way, and of course, by helping others, you always get a great reward.

Now, with all this talk about purpose and love, remember, you gotta have self-love. If you don't love yourself, you won't be able to feel or love others. So that's gotta be the first thing you work on - boosting your self-esteem. Then, I suggest setting goals, writing them down daily, not resting until you achieve them, and I guarantee you won't feel like this again. On the contrary, you'll feel full of love.

One very important thing - the opposite of love is fear. Keep that in mind. And once you can express love for yourself and others, comes bravery, honor, and a whole bunch of positive values. From the bottom of my heart, I hope this message, which is a summary of many of my own experiences that have helped me in my life, can help you too.

content.y:
Hey, **G**

Honestly, if your body is "relaxing" as you say. .

Maybe try stopping at that **point**, wait **10-20** seconds, then pump out **15** more.

The **Goal** would be to force your body to adapt to the new **max** repetitions you've set for it.

**The Human body is highly adaptable, you simply need more control.**

I will sometimes verbally tell myself or rather my body to "**Stop it!**", "**Adapt!**"


I'll also just give you insight into my own fitness real quick, in case that could help you or any other **G's**.


I usually do between **25-40** Pushups, depending on how many pushups in **total** I want to do.

If I "lose" count, I add at least 2-5 more.

Once I'm finished, I know I either hit the number I wanted or I went a bit over.

If I want to do **100** I'll either pump out as many as I can then rest for **30** seconds or less then finish.

Or I'll do sets of **25**.

I'll give myself a **max 2 and a half minute break**.

If I want to do 500/600 in less than an hour, I won't be able to afford big breaks.

**(Unless I want to do big sets, which might allow bigger breaks)**

For me personally, after about 150 or so, the "burning" sensation stops. .

and my muscles literally just give out at the end of a set of pushups, simple as that.

Break, go again. 

(One time I had barely **5¬†min** left to beat the **60¬†min** Timer I set for myself.
I could only do max **5-10** repetitions with **15-30sec** rest)



Hopefully this helps.

If there is another issue, then approach it with the same mindset and courage. Remember to always be a gentleman and if at any point you need to walk away so that you aren't strung along then do so (even if it hurts). In my school we had a national economics project, where you had to create your own business attend markets, enterprise presentations and pitches. What I definitely learned that year the most is, that preparation is key. If you are confident and know what to present you immediately display professionality and show that you know what you want. Also when talking to customers I've learned how to approach them with a more professional "speech", which also made me feel like the wanted to buy the product rather than showing a feeling of "I have to buy this product from these amateurs".
By the time I could tell which teams prepared themselfs and knew what they wanted and which just "learned" their speech instead of being able to actually telling the listeners what enterprise they represent.

So, Firstly I'm not a coach and not here to teach basics. My assumption is you Already know the basics. I could do a whole other post on the way you position your feet but it's kind of difficult when talking here in TRW chat. Limitations. 

So, This is just a tip, but don't take it as a tip. Take it as a Prescription. If you Don't do this - you're gonna get hit at some point. 

When I get my point across you'll realize how incredibly simple and obvious it seems, but nobody does it. You don't think about it until you do. 

Let's use a hook for example:
When throwing a hook they teach you to protect your chin with your arm/shoulder using the arm you're hooking with. This is because even if you're throwing anything at all, you should Always be protected. 
Implement this with jabs too. Even when throwing a jab, you should still be protecting that side of your chin.

I attached images of what NOT to do - labeled so, and what TO Do - Labeled So. 

You should now understand what I'm getting at. When hooking, You keep your chin protected with your arm/shoulder. 

Do this with Jabs ALSO. Throw straight, fast, exactly how you would - but tuck that side of your chin into your arm. 

ALWAYS Block Your Face.
